existing_answers.agent_a:
To center a div horizontally:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
}
```

For both horizontal and vertical centering:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

existing_answers.agent_b:
Modern approach using CSS Grid:
```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

Or using margin auto for horizontal centering:
```css
.centered {
  max-width: 600px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

existing_answers.agent_c:
Classic approach with absolute positioning:
```css
.centered {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}
```

All methods work well, choice depends on your layout needs.
